# Backend Rules — aide

## Layering

- Route handlers orchestrate only — no business logic in controllers
- Business rules live in `src/domain/`
- Persistence and external calls live in `src/infrastructure/`

## API Contracts

- Validate input at the boundary with explicit schemas
- Return consistent error shape: `{ error: { code, message } }`
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes

## Data Access

- No raw SQL in controllers
- Parameterized queries only — no string concatenation
- Transactions for multi-step writes

## Errors & Logging

- Log structured JSON with correlation ID
- Never expose stack traces in production responses
- Fail closed on auth failures

## Reference

- Architecture: `docs/architecture.md`
- Standards: `docs/coding-standards.md`

## Prohibited

- Direct DB access from presentation layer
- Catching exceptions without handling or rethrowing
- Hard-coded secrets or connection strings
